modules.description: Provides functions for composing and executing asynchronous workflows using Lwt, including parallel and sequential execution of tasks, error handling, and result aggregation. Operates on lists of Lwt promises and custom pipeline stages represented as functions. Used to build efficient data processing pipelines in networked applications, such as parallel API requests with aggregated results.

Provides synchronous and asynchronous transformation steps for processing data streams, including error mapping, result handling, and key tracking. Operates on input-output pairs, result types, and tuples containing keys. Used to build and execute pipelines that maintain input order while applying serial or parallel transformations, and to separate successful and error results from a stream.
